Nyia Parler, 41, allegedly left her quadriplegic son, 21, with just a blanket and a bible in Pennsylvania woods on Monday .
Police say she left him there, before going to stay with her boyfriend, John Ferguson, in Maryland .
On Sunday, she allegedly wheeled her son into a park near Philadelphia and left him in a wheelchair .
Parler has been charged with aggravated assault, reckless endangering, unlawful restraint and false imprisonment .